  <mads:note type="source">Wikipedia. "Persius, in full Aulus Persius Flaccus (Volterra, 34-62),
        was a Roman poet and satirist of Etruscan origin. In his works, poems and satires, he shows
        a stoic wisdom and a strong criticism for the abuses of his contemporaries. His works, which
        became very popular in the Middle Ages, were published after his death by his friend and
        mentor the stoic philosopher Lucius Annaeus Cornutus...."</mads:note>
  
